{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "CO2Equilibria",
        "description": "CO2 dissolution and dissociation equilibria with van't Hoff temperature dependence (Seinfeld & Pandis Ch 7 §7.3.2, Eqs 7.14–7.24). Migrated from Aerosol.jl@c8c640bb src/aqueous_equilibria.jl:140 (`CO2Equilibria` @component). Parameterized as observed-only: T, H_plus, p_CO2 are inputs and the carbonate-system species (CO2_aq, HCO3-, CO3^2-, total dissolved C, effective Henry constant) are algebraic outputs.",
        "tags": [
            "aerosol",
            "aqueous_equilibria",
            "observed-only",
            "seinfeld-pandis"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-06T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "Aerosol.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (mdl-5b1)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., & Pandis, S. N. (2016). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 3rd ed. Wiley. Chapter 7, Section 7.3.2 (CO2 dissolution and dissociation, Eqs 7.14–7.24) and Table 7.4 (equilibrium-constant temperature dependence). ISBN 978-1-118-94740-1."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "CO2Equilibria": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: Aerosol.jl@c8c640bb:src/aqueous_equilibria.jl:140\nUpstream `CO2Equilibria` is an MTK `@component` where T, H_plus, and p_CO2 are `@variables` driven by a parent `AqueousEquilibria` system. For standalone serialization (and to make the component well-posed in isolation), they are declared as parameters here — matching the bead's `(S, observed-only)` classification. The seven algebraic equations are unchanged from upstream.\n\nNote on dH_Kc1: upstream Aerosol.jl literal is 7657.12 J/mol (1.83 kcal/mol per S&P Table 7.4 with 1 kcal = 4184 J nominally yields 7656.72; the upstream value is preserved verbatim for bit-for-bit fidelity with the source — see source_ref).\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-6): observed-only algebraic system (no ODE integration); 1e-6 covers float64 roundoff in the chained exp/multiply/divide expressions of the van't Hoff K_c1/K_c2/H_CO2 closed forms across the atmospheric T range (273–318 K) and multi-decade [H+]/p_CO2 sweeps, including the H_CO2_eff sum which adds K_c1*K_c2/[H+]^2 (small for [H+]>1e-7 mol/m^3 but reaches O(1) at high pH)."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-6
            },
            "variables": {
                "T": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 298.0,
                    "description": "Temperature"
                },
                "H_plus": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "mol/m^3",
                    "default": 0.0001,
                    "description": "Hydrogen ion concentration (1e-4 mol/m^3 = pH 7 in pure water at 298 K)"
                },
                "p_CO2": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "Pa",
                    "default": 40.0,
                    "description": "Partial pressure of CO2 (≈ 400 ppm at 1 atm = 40.5 Pa; rounded to 40 Pa)"
                },
                "R_gas": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/mol/K",
                    "default": 8.314,
                    "description": "Gas constant"
                },
                "T_ref": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 298.0,
                    "description": "Reference temperature"
                },
                "H_CO2_298": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "mol/m^3/Pa",
                    "default": 0.0003355539106834444,
                    "description": "Henry's law constant for CO2 at 298 K (3.4e-2 M/atm × 1000 mol·m⁻³/M ÷ 101325 Pa/atm)"
                },
                "dH_H_CO2": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/mol",
                    "default": -20292.4,
                    "description": "Heat of dissolution for CO2 (-4.85 kcal/mol converted to J/mol; Seinfeld & Pandis Table 7.4)"
                },
                "K_c1_298": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "mol/m^3",
                    "default": 4.3e-4,
                    "description": "First dissociation constant K_c1 at 298 K (4.3e-7 M × 1000 mol·m⁻³/M)"
                },
                "K_c2_298": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "mol/m^3",
                    "default": 4.7e-8,
                    "description": "Second dissociation constant K_c2 at 298 K (4.7e-11 M × 1000 mol·m⁻³/M)"
                },
                "dH_Kc1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/mol",
                    "default": 7657.12,
                    "description": "Enthalpy for K_c1 (1.83 kcal/mol; upstream literal preserved verbatim per source_ref)"
                },
                "dH_Kc2": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/mol",
                    "default": 14853.2,
                    "description": "Enthalpy for K_c2 (3.55 kcal/mol converted to J/mol)"
                },
                "H_CO2": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "mol/m^3/Pa",
                    "description": "Henry's law constant for CO2 at temperature T"
                },
                "K_c1": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "mol/m^3",
                    "description": "First dissociation constant K_c1 at temperature T"
                },
                "K_c2": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "mol/m^3",
                    "description": "Second dissociation constant K_c2 at temperature T"
                },
                "CO2_aq": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "mol/m^3",
                    "description": "Aqueous CO2 concentration [CO2·H2O]"
                },
                "HCO3_minus": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "mol/m^3",
                    "description": "Bicarbonate concentration [HCO3-]"
                },
                "CO3_2minus": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "mol/m^3",
                    "description": "Carbonate concentration [CO3^2-]"
                },
                "C_total": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "mol/m^3",
                    "description": "Total dissolved inorganic carbon (CO2_aq + HCO3- + CO3^2-)"
                },
                "H_CO2_eff": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "mol/m^3/Pa",
                    "description": "Effective Henry's law constant for CO2 (S&P Eq 7.24)"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "H_CO2",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            "H_CO2_298",
                            {
                                "op": "exp",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "/", "args": ["dH_H_CO2", "R_gas"] },
                                            {
                                                "op": "+",
                                                "args": [
                                                    { "op": "/", "args": [1, "T_ref"] },
                                                    { "op": "/", "args": [-1, "T"] }
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "K_c1",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            "K_c1_298",
                            {
                                "op": "exp",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            -1,
                                            { "op": "/", "args": ["dH_Kc1", "R_gas"] },
                                            {
                                                "op": "+",
                                                "args": [
                                                    { "op": "/", "args": [1, "T"] },
                                                    { "op": "/", "args": [-1, "T_ref"] }
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "K_c2",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            "K_c2_298",
                            {
                                "op": "exp",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            -1,
                                            { "op": "/", "args": ["dH_Kc2", "R_gas"] },
                                            {
                                                "op": "+",
                                                "args": [
                                                    { "op": "/", "args": [1, "T"] },
                                                    { "op": "/", "args": [-1, "T_ref"] }
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "CO2_aq",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": ["H_CO2", "p_CO2"]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "HCO3_minus",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            { "op": "*", "args": ["K_c1", "CO2_aq"] },
                            "H_plus"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "CO3_2minus",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            { "op": "*", "args": ["K_c2", "HCO3_minus"] },
                            "H_plus"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "C_total",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": ["CO2_aq", "HCO3_minus", "CO3_2minus"]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "H_CO2_eff",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            "H_CO2",
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    1,
                                    { "op": "/", "args": ["K_c1", "H_plus"] },
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "*", "args": ["K_c1", "K_c2"] },
                                            { "op": "^", "args": ["H_plus", 2] }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "self_consistency_298K_pH7",
                    "description": "Reference state: 298 K, pH 7 ([H+] = 1e-4 mol/m³), p_CO2 = 40 Pa (≈400 ppm). All temperature-dependent constants collapse to their 298 K values: H_CO2 = H_CO2_298, K_c1 = K_c1_298, K_c2 = K_c2_298. Validates the closed-form algebra at the reference point with no exp() drift.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 298.0,
                        "H_plus": 1.0e-4,
                        "p_CO2": 40.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "H_CO2",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0003355539106834444 },
                        { "variable": "K_c1",        "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.00043 },
                        { "variable": "K_c2",        "time": 0.0, "expected": 4.7e-08 },
                        { "variable": "CO2_aq",      "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.013422156427337776 },
                        { "variable": "HCO3_minus",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.05771527263755243 },
                        { "variable": "CO3_2minus",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 2.712617813964964e-05 },
                        { "variable": "C_total",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.07116455524302986 },
                        { "variable": "H_CO2_eff",   "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0017791138810757466 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "vant_hoff_273K_pH7",
                    "description": "Cold cloud water at 273.15 K, pH 7. Exothermic CO2 dissolution (ΔH = -4.85 kcal/mol) increases H_CO2 with cooling; K_c1 and K_c2 shift per their van't Hoff enthalpies. Exercises the cold-end T sweep.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 273.15,
                        "H_plus": 1.0e-4,
                        "p_CO2": 40.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "H_CO2",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0007069168810207723 },
                        { "variable": "K_c1",        "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.00032460796806137697 },
                        { "variable": "K_c2",        "time": 0.0, "expected": 2.72415349942885e-08 },
                        { "variable": "H_CO2_eff",   "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0030022505182105727 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "vant_hoff_310K_pH7",
                    "description": "Warm water at 310 K, pH 7. H_CO2 decreases with warming (exothermic dissolution); K_c1, K_c2 increase. Exercises the warm-end T sweep.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 310.0,
                        "H_plus": 1.0e-4,
                        "p_CO2": 40.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "H_CO2",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.00024438220555187627 },
                        { "variable": "K_c1",        "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0004846467802289126 },
                        { "variable": "K_c2",        "time": 0.0, "expected": 5.9276595766723254e-08 },
                        { "variable": "H_CO2_eff",   "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0014294747625748952 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "vant_hoff_318K_pH7",
                    "description": "Upper-range temperature for atmospheric aqueous-phase chemistry (45°C).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 318.0,
                        "H_plus": 1.0e-4,
                        "p_CO2": 40.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "H_CO2",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.00020046922438973815 },
                        { "variable": "K_c1",        "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0005222575943612809 },
                        { "variable": "K_c2",        "time": 0.0, "expected": 6.85247903946315e-08 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "acidic_pH4",
                    "description": "Acidic cloud water at pH 4 (typical polluted rain), 298 K, ambient p_CO2. Increased [H+] suppresses HCO3- and CO3^2- (1/[H+] and 1/[H+]^2 dependence), so H_CO2_eff → H_CO2 (the dissociation correction vanishes).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 298.0,
                        "H_plus": 0.1,
                        "p_CO2": 40.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "CO2_aq",      "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.013422156427337776 },
                        { "variable": "HCO3_minus",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 5.771527263755243e-05 },
                        { "variable": "CO3_2minus",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 2.7126178139649634e-11 },
                        { "variable": "H_CO2_eff",   "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.00033699679317753764 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "basic_pH9",
                    "description": "Basic cloud water at pH 9, 298 K, ambient p_CO2. Reduced [H+] amplifies HCO3- (∝ 1/[H+]) and CO3^2- (∝ 1/[H+]^2); H_CO2_eff is dominated by the dissociation terms.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 298.0,
                        "H_plus": 1.0e-6,
                        "p_CO2": 40.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "CO2_aq",      "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.013422156427337776 },
                        { "variable": "HCO3_minus",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 5.771527263755243 },
                        { "variable": "CO3_2minus",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.2712617813964964 },
                        { "variable": "C_total",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 6.056211201579078 },
                        { "variable": "H_CO2_eff",   "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.15140528003947692 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "coupled_cold_acidic",
                    "description": "Cross-check: cold (273.15 K) AND acidic (pH 4). Combines the van't Hoff temperature shift on all three K constants with the [H+] sweep.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 273.15,
                        "H_plus": 0.1,
                        "p_CO2": 40.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "H_CO2",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0007069168810207723 },
                        { "variable": "CO2_aq",      "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.028276675240830895 },
                        { "variable": "HCO3_minus",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 9.178834093457564e-05 },
                        { "variable": "H_CO2_eff",   "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0007092115901692506 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "coupled_warm_basic",
                    "description": "Cross-check: warm (310 K) AND basic (pH 9). Both K_c1 and K_c2 shift up; carbonate-system speciation is dominated by HCO3- and CO3^2-.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 310.0,
                        "H_plus": 1.0e-6,
                        "p_CO2": 40.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "H_CO2",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.00024438220555187627 },
                        { "variable": "CO2_aq",      "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.009775288222075051 },
                        { "variable": "HCO3_minus",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 4.737561962638284 },
                        { "variable": "CO3_2minus",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.28082654537911367 },
                        { "variable": "C_total",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 5.028163796239473 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "high_p_CO2",
                    "description": "Elevated CO2 partial pressure (1000 ppm ≈ 101 Pa) at 298 K, pH 7. CO2_aq scales linearly with p_CO2 (Henry's law), and all derived speciation scales accordingly. Exercises the p_CO2 axis.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 298.0,
                        "H_plus": 1.0e-4,
                        "p_CO2": 101.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "CO2_aq",      "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.033890944979027886 },
                        { "variable": "HCO3_minus",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.1457310634098199 },
                        { "variable": "C_total",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.17969050198865041 }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": []
        }
    }
}
